"Juda-Rezler K.","New challenges in air quality and climate modeling",2010,"Archives of Environmental Protection","36","1",,"3","28",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-76949107607&partnerID=40&md5=e830f6fa5895b0e295d97441e376a3fd","Warsaw University of Technology, Faculty of Environmental Engineering, Air Pollution Control Group, ul. Nowowiejska 20, 00-653 Warszawa, Poland","Juda-Rezler, K., Warsaw University of Technology, Faculty of Environmental Engineering, Air Pollution Control Group, ul. Nowowiejska 20, 00-653 Warszawa, Poland","At present, when high particulate matter (PM) concentrations in ambient air cause thousands of premature deaths in Europe and global climate change is becoming the most critical issue in environmental protection, the state-of-the-scicncc air quality and climate models constitute an essential research as well as decision support tools. Recently the great progress has been achieved in this research area. The present paper presents the goals and tools for Air Quality (AQ) Modeling, and gives overview of current challenges, including the meteorological, chemistry and climate modeling. The main emphasis is given to the regulatory and the Eulerian grid models, the latter arc currently operating as so called off-line or on-line modeling systems. The issues connected with model implementation and validation is presented as well. Finally, the conclusions are drawn and recommendations for further development and integration of AQ and climate modeling in Poland arc presented. © Copyright by institute of Envionmental Engineering of the Polish Academy of Sciences.","Air quality; Air quality models; Chemical mechanisms; Climate change; Meteorological models; Regional climate models",,,,,,,"Abert, K., Budiñski, K., Juda-Rezler, K., Regional air pollution models for Poland (1994) Ecological Engineering, 3, pp. 225-244; Barlnicki, J., Hrchoruk, J., Grzybowska, A., Mazur, A., Regional model for atmospheric transport of heavy metals o